RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALO STYLE had a good position three wide outside tracking the early front duo, engaged three wide midway on the turn, took control four deep at the top of the lane and was kept to the task to win comfortably at the finish. MY GIRL GABBY settled near the rear at the half, rallied three wide outside foes following the path of the winner throughout the turn, angled out five wide to be the threat at the top of the stretch and chased but to no avail to the finish. ITS A BIRDIE was bumped at the start to be near the rear down the backside, took closer order inside running early on the turn, was on hold looking for a seam entering the stretch, shifted off the tiring front runners in the four path at the furlong marker and offered a good finish to close in capturing third money. JUNGLE TIGRESS had a good spot behind the contesting top two into the turn, was in tight surroundings nearing the five sixteenth pole, was checked briefly. MANITOULIN ISLAND was unhurried in the early stages of the race trailing the field turning for home and could only pass the tired engaging frontrunners to the wire. MURDER HORNET had a narrow advantage just outside taking the field into the turn, battled upfront between horses with five sixteenths to the wire, was collared outside by the winner at the top of the lane and yielded on the rail in the last sixteenth. NATASHA'S BIZNIZ pressed the issue on the rail down the back straight, was scrubbed on dueling inside for the lead midpoint on the turn and retreated on the fence in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEED CHESS was content tracking the loose pacesetter down the backside, began to reel in the frontrunner midway on the final turn, assumed command inside at the eighth pole and was edging away in the final sixteenth for the victory. KIMONO KATE was keen early to get to the rail taking this field into the first turn, continued up front opening up on rivals down the backstretch, was collared by the winner inside at the furlong marker and gave way grudgingly in the last sixteenth. P. S. RISING STAR was bumped on the break, regrouped to track on the rail in the second flight down the back straight, battled two wide outside for third money on the far turn and put in a good finish to secure a non threatening third in the end. LEADING FORCE broke out at the start, tracked on the rail at the half mile marker, put in a brief rally on the fence at the three eighths pole and stalled in mid stretch to settle for a minor role at the finish. SILENT CREEK stalked near the rear at the half, advanced on the fence throughout the second turn, angled out three wide for the drive and was only one paced to the wire. TAKE CHANCES was pinballed between horses on the break, settled near the back with four furlongs remaining, was ridden for more at the three eighths marker, shifted out to the five path at the top of the stretch but only made little impact down the lane. LOADED MISTRESS broke out at the start, settled outside in midfield outside foes at the half, could not match strides with fellow runners three deep at the three furlong marker and faded when turning for home. SMART IRENE was allowed to settle trailing the field down the backstretch, saved ground at the back of the pack through the final turn and could not get involved driving to the finish line.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALLIE'S HERO made a good move with five eighths left to run to have a nice inside position behind the contesting leaders, waited patiently throughout the turn looking for a path to offer a run, decided to shift inwards to the fence at the three sixteenth marker to burst inside for the lead at the furlong pole and was kept to the task late to hold safe for the win. MALIBU SECRET had a good spot outside tracking in the second flight watching the front duo set the fractions, angled out four wide at the top of the stretch to take command but could not hold off the winner that was full of run on the rail in the final furlong. DIXIE GIANT tracked between horses in the second flight at the five eighths pole, was on hold behind horses through the turn, looked for a seam four deep in upper stretch, shifted in to the two path at the furlong marker and closed well to capture third at the wire. TAKE A CHANCE broke out at the start, contested for the lead on the rail running on the turn, was headed on both sides in upper stretch, determinedly fought on in the late stages but was on the losing end of a three horse photo in a gritty effort. FORESTER'S TURN settled near the rear in the early going, put in a mild turn of foot four wide keeping position at the three furlong marker, shifted to the five path for the stretch drive and evened out at the furlong marker. SEA SCOUT was bumped lightly at the start, trailed the field two furlongs from the wire angling out to be six wide, shifted out widest in the eight path in mid stretch for clear run and offered little finish to the line. COMBATIVE trailed in the three path down the backstretch, offered a brief run four wide outside three furlongs from home, was in the mix six deep for a small share at the three sixteenth marker and faded in deep stretch. ALICIA'S KID dueled for the front outside on the turn, was collared with rivals on either side at the quarter marker and stopped with a furlong left to run.

HEART BOY settled at the rear shifting in two wide, lacked room racing at the back inside and in behind rivals, bided time then began to advance while tipping out a bit on the far turn, angled seven wide into upper stretch, was left with far too much to do but got up for show honors without threatening the winner or making late headway on the runner-up. PASSIONPLATE sped clear, set the pace racing off the rail, weakened in the stretch. MANETKA settled at the back three wide, began to move on the far turn while tipping out from four to six wide, angled outside foes in upper stretch eight deep and ran on well but too late. RARE DISCOVERY gained forward position stalking the pacesetter three wide, applied a tad of pressure up the backstretch, lacked the needed late kick. SNOOKERED was forwardly-placed three to four wide stalking just in behind and outside the leading rivals, was close up heading up the backstretch, dropped back some heading to the far turn and shifted in a bit racing two to three wide on that bend, asked for more at the quarter pole, failed to rally. WIKWEMIKONG GHOST was in tight after the break, encouraged along two to three wide between runners early but lacking speed, swung out five wide for the stretch run, failed to menace. DOC FISHMAN was a bit slow to gather, caught four to five wide outside foes toward the back in the early going, failed to threaten. WIN THE DRAW raced off the pace saving ground through both turns, was put to urging three furlongs out but had no response and failed to rally. UNBRIDLED INFERNO cleared the field and shifted in, settled along the rail to track the leader from inside, came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARALINGA had a good trip sitting on the fence behind the engaging threesome throughout the turn, slipped up the rail in upper stretch, took command at the eighth pole and just had enough left late to hold on for the win crossing the wire. TAPPING A RHYTHM contested for the front between rivals in the two path running on the turn, bid for the lead four wide with numerous runners involved with three sixteenths remaining, gamely dug in when passed by the winner at the eighth pole and re-rallied late to make it close at the wire. GRACE ON THE GREEN sat alone rating kindly in the third flight with four furlongs left to run, loomed the threat six wide angling out for the stretch drive and closed outside runners to get up for third winning the nod at the finish. SMILES FOR DAVID was coaxed for more inside with a half left to run, rallied behind the leaders three deep to be involved at the top of the stretch, shifted into the rail for the final eighth and finished up well on the fence just missed the photo for third money at the wire. SILENT SKY had a good position beside the winner running outside through the turn, shifted out to the five path for the stretch drive to be in with a chance in mid stretch but could not find another gear to contend in the late stages of the race. WHERE'S SAMNBAILEY travelled in the middle of the pack two deep on the turn, angled out to be widest in the seven path turning for home and finished up evenly to the wire in the final eighth. BURLAP broke inwards bumping rival at the start, travelled near the back throughout the turn, angled out into the eight path at the top of the lane, lacked room, dipped in to the four path at the three sixteenth pole to start picking up runners and had no room to extend her stride late in deep stretch. RAVELLO BEAUTY broke at the start bumping fellow rival to begin, stalked near the rear three wide early on, angled out six wide for the stretch run and passed tired runners. SILENT TRIBUTE prompted the pace scenario three wide at the half, was still in the mix of things five wide turning for home and tired between runners at the furlong marker. KRYPTO GAINS had a narrow lead on the rail with two others rivals contesting up front at the half, was collared by runners at the three sixteenth pole and stopped deep stretch. GOLDEN SUZIE was unhurried from the outside early, got the to rail to trail the field down the backside, saved ground running on the turn and showed little interest driving to the wire. SNOW LAKE settled near the rear just outside in the early going, was roused at the top of the stretch and could not find another gear to be a factor to the finish.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 9 7 1/2F Inner turf CR: 69. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. INNER TURF FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORMIN DAVE shifted in to the three to four path about mid-pack early, steadily advanced early up the backstretch, eased back off rivals on the far turn then angled outside those to enter the top of the stretch seven wide and full of run, drifted in while taking the lead by mid-stretch but kicked clear. TREBUCHET stalked two to three wide, bid briefly in upper stretch but was no match for the winner, kept on and just saved second. AIR FORCE RESERVE was checked sharply after the start then coaxed along two to three wide to gain more forward position, raced about mid-pack, continued three wide on the far turn, came out in the stretch, rallied and just missed second by a short nose. BARTICA saved ground racing inside early in the back half of the field, gained closer contact with the leaders on the far turn, lacked room in behind two to three wide past the quarter pole briefly, came out in upper stretch and kicked on just mildly once clear. HEY LUIGI prompted the pace two to three wide, took the lead about the five-sixteenths, was overtaken in upper stretch and lacked the needed late kick. NGABE bumped a rival fairly hard at the start, lacked early speed dropping well back off the leaders, saved ground to the quarter pole, shifted out swinging nine wide into upper stretch, finished strongest of all but far too late. DEFOGGER was bumped at the start, recovered quickly to gain forward position inside tracking the leaders, came out a bit on the far turn, weakened in the stretch. TAYBO set a pressured pace inside, wilted. RIVER OF BABYLON broke outwardly then veered in a bit to correct, went four to five wide on the first turn inside foes but forced wide by an inside rival, advanced rapidly up the backstretch from outside to be within striking distance, continued wide on the far turn in range, faltered and faded. DIO BRANDO was a bit unprepared at the start and consequently away slowly, was caught seven wide into the first turn but eased back and angled in, raced well back and saved ground along the rail on the far turn, made no bid. GUESS I'M BEST received a saddle adjustment at the gate, was squeezed back at the start, caught five to six wide on the first turn, dropped back, was pulled up near the five-sixteenths and vanned off. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF BARTICA AGAINST AIR FORCE RESERVE ALLEGING INTERFERENCE COMING TO THE TOP OF THE STRETCH NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
